This paper deals with game theory and cryptography, which are both central topics in computer science. The paper discusses the ability to implement mediators using cheap talk, which is a communication protocol commonly used in distributed systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
